<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-07-26T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-07-26T08:00:00-05:00" n="294" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d294">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">123 S1 1/80: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harvey</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-07-26T14:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">July 26,
                                        1922—2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received July 26—9:58
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>312. Your 217, July 20, 3 p.m. Investigation now proceeding. Embassy has
                            informally communicated to the Foreign Office its assumption that actual
                            withdrawal of recognition will not be proceeded with until opportunity
                            has been given to develop and confirm pertinent facts.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Harvey</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>